3.The preparation of the accompanying Statement is the responsibility of the Management of the Company. This responsibility includes designing, implementing and maintaining internal control relevant to the preparation and presentation of the Statement, and applying an appropriate basis of preparation; and making estimates that are reasonable in the circumstances.			
4.We conducted our examination of the Statement in accordance with the Guidance Note on Reports or Certificates for Special Purposes issued by the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India.			
5. Accordingly, we do not accept or assume any liability or any duty of care for any other purpose or to any other person to whom this certificate is shown or into whose hands it may come without our prior consent in writing			
6. While computing withdrawls from the bank account, we have considered total receipts during the period and balance lying in RERA Bank Account as base for computing withdrawable amount on account of construction. Moreover the promotoers have parked 100% the amount received from the customers in the RERA account as against the requirement of 70%			
7 The details related to date of agreement of sale and contact details has been given based on the details provided by the management			
8. The management has not provided the details related to booked covered and booked open parking so details is not given.
